LinkedHashMap in Java implements the Map interface of the Collections Framework. It stores key-value pairs while maintaining the insertion order of the entries. It maintains the order in which elements are added.
‚Ä¢ Stores unique key-value pairs.
‚Ä¢ Maintains insertion order.
‚Ä¢ Allows one null key and multiple null values.
‚Ä¢ It is not thread-safe; to synchronize it, use Collections.synchronizedMap().

-> Declaration of LinkedHashMap
    public class LinkedHashMap<K,‚ÄãV> extends HashMap<K,‚ÄãV> implements Map<K,‚ÄãV>

Here, K is the key Object type and V is the value Object type
‚Ä¢ K: The type of keys in the map.
‚Ä¢ V: The type of values mapped in the map.

